==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Oxanilide
<hw>Ox*an"i*lide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Ox</ets>alic + <ets>anil</ets>ine + am<ets>ide</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A white crystalline substance, resembling
oxanilamide, obtained by heating aniline oxalate, and regarded as a
double anilide of oxalic acid; -- called also <altname>diphenyl
oxamide</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

